(Tomorrowville seeps the grotesque jollity
of an attorney in a clown suit. The
cheerful blue pathway clashes sharply with
the synthetic turf around it, a scraggly
mat colored in the friendly hue of clotted
blood. The fact that everything is so
neatly organized only regiments the
unpleasantness.

The buildings are no more attractive. The
observation tower, a grotesque spire,
looks like it's ready to topple, which
would actually be an improvement, as it
would likely crush the grey building to
its left, a monolithic structure that
shows no sign of light or shadow on
its plain surface, a greedy sponge
absorbing the sunlight.

This place is is as ugly as a ZZT dialog
box.)

    end
